text.section:
The Mayor and City Council of Baltimore City or the governing body of a county or of a municipal corporation may grant, by law, a property tax credit against the county or municipal corporation property tax imposed on rental dwellings of owners who provide reduced rents for any tenant who:
is at least 65 years old;
has been found permanently and totally disabled and has qualified for benefits under:
the Social Security Act;
the Railroad Retirement Act;
any federal act for members of the United States armed forces; or
any federal retirement system; or
has been found permanently and totally disabled by a county health officer or the Baltimore City Commissioner of Health.

The county or municipal corporation may provide, by law, for:
the specific requirements for eligibility for a tax credit authorized under this section;
additional limitations on eligibility for the credit;
the amount and duration of the credit; and
any other provision appropriate to implement the credit.
